# ============================================================================
#  slacker — repository priorities & sources          (slackware64-current)
# ============================================================================
#
#  Format — one repo per line:
#        [priority]   [name]   [url]   [flags]
#
#    * Higher priority WINS when the same package name exists in several repos.
#    * To pull from a LOWER-priority repo on purpose, use   name:package
#      (e.g.  alienbob:vlc).
#    * An installed package is never silently migrated to another repo nor
#      downgraded — only a repo of HIGHER OR EQUAL priority may replace it.
#    * Every repo needs a DISTINCT priority (tag lines at the bottom may share).
#
#  The official repo's url is the keyword  mirror  — slacker fills it in from
#  the active line in the 'mirrors' file. Change your mirror in
#  /etc/slacker/mirrors;  here you set only its priority / placement.
#
#  Flags:  official | immutable | subtree | verify=...   (reference below)
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Active repositories
# [priority]  [name]      [url]              [flags]
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
100         slackware   mirror              official
200         patches     mirror/patches      subtree immutable
90          extras      mirror/extra        subtree immutable
85          testing     mirror/testing      subtree immutable
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  More repos — uncomment, tune the priority to your needs, or add your own.
#  (Append flags at the end if needed, e.g. immutable / verify=...)
