#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Flags reference
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  official    The tracked distro repo: powers show-changelog and is the
#              default for install-new. Placement is still by priority only.
#  immutable   clean-system never removes packages attributed to this repo —
#              use it for extra / testing / patches you keep installed.
#  subtree     The url is a Slackware distribution subtree (extra, patches,
#              testing, pasture): metadata is read FROM the url, but packages
#              and GPG-KEY are fetched from the parent (root). The four subtrees
#              MUST carry this flag, or their packages 404.
#  verify=...  Per-repo override of the global VERIFY (slacker.conf) for THAT
#              repo only. Values:  all | none | a comma list of gpg,md5,sha.
#              Order relative to 'official' does not matter. Use it when one
#              repo ships a broken/missing checksum or signature, so you relax
#              only that repo instead of weakening everything. Examples:
#                100  slackware  mirror                                                   official  verify=gpg,md5
#                80   conraid    https://slackers.it/repository/slackware64-current                 verify=gpg,md5
#                60   alienbob   https://slackware.nl/people/alien/sbrepos/current/x86_64           verify=md5
#
# ============================================================================
#  Source / build-tag priorities
#       [priority]   [name]   [tag]
# ============================================================================
#  Packages built from NON-repository sources (SlackBuilds.org, your own local
#  builds) carry a build tag after the build number — e.g.  _SBo, _rtz.  Give
#  those tags a priority on the SAME scale as the repos above, so upgrade-all
#  treats them as a prioritised source: a tagged package is only replaced by a
#  candidate from a repo of HIGHER OR EQUAL priority.
#
#  Keep them HIGH so your SBo / local packages are never silently migrated to
#  conraid / alienbob / etc. or downgraded — upgrade those via sbopkg / sbotools
#  / slpkg instead.  (Tag lines, unlike repos, MAY share a priority.)
#
#  Format:  [priority]  [name]   [tag]
#
#100        SBo         _SBo
#100        local       YOURTAG
#
# ============================================================================
